1 each year with its annual statement a medical dental loss ratio report with the commissioner of securities and
2 insurance that is organized by market and product type and contains similar information required in the 2013
3 federal medical loss ratio annual reporting form. The filing must also report additional data that includes the
4 number of enrollees, the annual maximum coverage limit, and the number of enrollees who meet or exceed the
5 annual coverage limit.
6 (2) (a) The dental loss ratio reporting year must be for the policy year during which dental
7 coverage is provided by the insurer. All terms used in the dental loss ratio annual report have the same
8 meaning as used in the federal Public Health Service Act, 42 U.S.C. 300gg-18, and 45 CFR, part 158.
9 (b) If data verification of the dental insurer's representations in the dental loss ratio annual report is
10 considered necessary, the commissioner shall provide the dental insurer with a notification of the additional
11 information needed within 30 days.
12 (c) The dental insurer has 30 days from the date of notification to submit to the commissioner all
13 requested data. The commissioner may extend the time for a dental insurer to comply with this subsection on a
14 finding of good cause.
15 (3) By January 1 of the year after the commissioner receives the dental loss ratio information
16 collected pursuant to [sections 1 through 5], the commissioner shall make the information, including the
17 aggregate dental loss ratio and other data reported pursuant to this section, available to the public in a
18 searchable format on a public website that allows members of the public to compare dental loss ratios among
19 insurers by plan type. The commissioner shall accomplish this by:
20 (a) posting the information on the department's website; and
21 (b) requiring the insurer to publish their specific information on the dental insurer's website.
22 (4) The commissioner shall report biennially the data in this section to the economic affairs interim
23 committee in accordance with 5-11-210.
