1 (B) on a pro rata basis; and
2 (C) if the ratio of the amount of premium revenue expended by the dental insurer on the costs for
3 reimbursement for services provided to policyholders or certificate holders to the total amount of premium
4 revenue, as reported in [section 3], is less than 80%.
5 (ii) The cost of activities that improve dental care quality may be added to the costs for
6 reimbursement in the calculation.
7 (b) The total amount of premium revenue must exclude federal and state taxes and licensing or
8 regulatory fees.
9 (c) The total amount of an annual rebate required under this section must equal the product of the
10 amount by which the percentage in (1)(a)(i)(C) exceeds the insurer's reported percentage in [section 3]
11 multiplied by the annual premium revenue less federal and state taxes and licensing or regulatory fees.
12 (2) A dental insurer shall provide any rebate owing to a policyholder or certificate holder no later
13 than August 1 of the calendar year following the year for which the ratio described in subsection (1) is
14 calculated.
